      "content": "### **How the Chair of Food Standards Scotland is Appointed**\n\nThe appointment process for the **Chair of Food Standards Scotland (FSS)** is governed by the **Food (Scotland) Act 2015**, which established FSS as a non-ministerial public body responsible for food safety, standards, and nutrition in Scotland.\n\n---\n\n#### **Key Provisions from the Food (Scotland) Act 2015**\n\n1. **Appointment by Scottish Ministers**\n   - The **Chair of Food Standards Scotland is appointed directly by the Scottish Ministers** (Section 6(1)(a)).\n   - The Scottish Ministers also appoint **between 3 and 7 additional members** to the FSS board (Section 6(1)(b)).\n\n2. **Eligibility Criteria**\n   - A person **cannot** be appointed as a member (including the Chair) if they are:\n     - A **member of the Scottish Parliament (MSP)**,\n     - A **member of the House of Commons**,\n     - A **member of the European Parliament**,\n     - An **office-holder in the Scottish Administration**,\n     - A **councillor of any local authority**, or\n     - An **employee of any local authority** (Section 6(2)).\n\n3. **Equal Opportunities Requirement**\n   - The Scottish Ministers must make appointments in a manner that **encourages equal opportunities**, particularly in observance of the **equal opportunity requirements** as defined in the **Scotland Act 1998** (Section 6(3)-(4)).\n\n4. **Term of Appointment**\n   - The **term and conditions** of the Chair\u2019s appointment are determined by the **Scottish Ministers** (Section 6(5)).\n   - A member (including the Chair) may **resign** by notifying the Scottish Ministers in writing (Section 6(6)).\n   - A member may be **re-appointed** after their term ends (Section 6(7)).\n\n5. **Early Termination of Appointment**\n   - The Scottish Ministers may **end a member\u2019s appointment** if:\n     - The member becomes **an undischarged bankrupt**,\n     - The member has been **absent from meetings for more than 6 consecutive months without permission**,\n     - The member is **unable to perform their functions**, or\n     - The member is **unsuitable to continue** (Section 7(2)).\n\n6. **Deputy Chair**\n   - The Scottish Ministers may assign one of the other members to **deputise for the Chair** or to **act as Chair** if there is a vacancy (Section 6(8)-(9)).\n\n---\n\n#### **Summary of the Appointment Process**\n1. **Nomination/Selection**: The Scottish Ministers identify a suitable candidate for the Chair position.\n2. **Appointment**: The Scottish Ministers formally appoint the Chair, ensuring they meet the eligibility criteria.\n3. **Term**: The Chair serves for a fixed term, as determined by the Scottish Ministers.\n4. **Reappointment/Removal**: The Chair may be reappointed or removed under specific conditions outlined in the Act.\n\n---\n#### **References**\n- **[Food (Scotland) Act 2015](http://www.legislation.gov.uk/asp/2015/1)** (Sections 6 and 7)."
